At the moment when generating the QR codes, they will show the entire URL plus the object ID. ex.:


{code:java}
<jirabaseurl>/secure/ShowObject.jspa?id=473
{code}


Please provide a way to customize the output of QR Codes, for example to output the object key.

h3. Problem Definition
The Jira REST API on api/2/issue returns inconsistent information on the Insight custom field in GET as compared to POST request - the JSON data for GET request includes the object's "label / name + object key" but the POST request only requires the "object key". The expectation for the REST API would be a consistent data.

 # Following [this guide|https://documentation.mindville.com/insight/latest/insight-with-jira-rest-api-33466746.html], create an issue via Jira REST API and include the key attribute to define the Insight object key(s). For example:
{code:java}
{
    "fields": {
       "project":
       {
          "key": "ITSD"
       },
       "summary": "REST ye merry gentlemen.",
       "description": "Creating of an issue using project keys and issue type names using the REST API",
       "issuetype": {
          "name": "Task"
       },
       "customfield_10300" : [{"key" : "IAS-1"}]
   }
}
{code}
(i) This will create an issue in project ITSD and associate object IAS-1 in an Insight custom field

 # Run the GET request to retrieve the data. For example:
{code:java}
{
  "expand": "renderedFields,names,schema,operations,editmeta,changelog,versionedRepresentations",
  "id": "10501",
  "self": "http://localhost:48133/j8133/rest/api/2/issue/10501",
  "key": "ITSD-44",
...
    "customfield_10300": [
      "iPhone 7 (IAS-1)"
    ],
{code}
(!) Notice the object name is included in the JSON data

Specifically, the difference is at:
{code:title=POST}
"customfield_10300" : [{"key" : "IAS-1"}]
{code}
{code:title=GET}
"customfield_10300": ["iPhone 7 (IAS-1)"],
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution
Return the same data format for both GET and POST.
 
h3. Workaround
No workaround available at this point of time.
